exercises.name: Warm Up
exercises.description: The warming up is a preparation for physical exertion or a performance by exercising or practising gently beforehand.

exercises.name: Bench Press
exercises.description: The bench press is an upper-body weight training exercise in which the trainee presses a weight upwards while lying on a weight training bench.

exercises.name: Glute Bridge
exercises.description: The bridge is an exercise. Many variations of this exercise are employed throughout the world, most commonly the balancing of the body on the head/shoulders and the feet.

exercises.name: Leg Raises
exercises.description: The leg raise is a strength training exercise which targets the iliopsoas (the anterior hip flexors).

exercises.name: Leg Press
exercises.description: The leg press is a weight training exercise in which the individual pushes a weight or resistance away from them using their legs.

exercises.name: Biceps Curls
exercises.description: The term biceps curl may refer to any of a number of weight training exercises that target the biceps brachii muscle.

exercises.name: Burpee
exercises.description: The burpee, or squat thrust, is a full body exercise used in strength training and as an aerobic exercise.

exercises.name: Butterfly
exercises.description: A Cable fly or Cable flye is a strength training exercise in which the hand and arm move through an arc while the elbow is kept at a constant angle.

exercises.name: Bicycling
exercises.description: Cycling, also called biking or bicycling, is the use of bicycles for transport, recreation, exercise or sport.

exercises.name: Hammer Curls
exercises.description: The term biceps curl may refer to any of a number of weight training exercises that target the biceps brachii muscle.

exercises.name: High Knees
exercises.description: In this exercise, you run forward or jog in place and bring your knees towards your chest.

exercises.name: Jogging
exercises.description: Jogging is a form of trotting or running at a slow or leisurely pace.

exercises.name: Kickbacks
exercises.description: The triceps kickback exercise works your triceps, which assist the chest in just about every pushing movement.

exercises.name: Pull Ups
exercises.description: A pull-up is an upper-body strength exercise. The pull-up is a closed-chain movement where the body is suspended by the hands and pulls up.

exercises.name: Squat
exercises.description: A squat is a strength exercise in which the trainee lowers their hips from a standing position and then stands back up.

exercises.name: Deadlift
exercises.description: The deadlift is a weight training exercise in which a loaded barbell or bar is lifted off the ground to the level of the hips, then lowered to the ground.

exercises.name: Barbell Curls
exercises.description: The term biceps curl may refer to any of a number of weight training exercises that target the biceps brachii muscle.

exercises.name: Barbell Row
exercises.description: A bent-over row (or barbell row) is a weight training exercise that targets a variety of back muscles.

exercises.name: Cable Pulldown
exercises.description: The pulldown exercise is a strength training exercise designed to develop the latissimus dorsi muscle.

exercises.name: Push Up
exercises.description: A push-up (or press-up) is a common calisthenics exercise beginning from the prone position, or the front leaning rest position known in the military.

exercises.name: Military Plank
exercises.description: The plank (also called a front hold, hover, or abdominal bridge) is an isometric core strength exercise that involves maintaining a position similar to a push-up for the maximum possible time.

exercises.name: Military Press
exercises.description: The press, overhead press or shoulder press is a weight training exercise with many variations, typically performed while standing, in which a weight is pressed straight upwards from racking position until the arms are locked out overhead, while the legs, lower back and abs maintain balance.

exercises.name: On Point Punches
exercises.description: On Point Punches is a relatively easy exercise, but you can still sweat quickly. You simply punch alternately and make steps in parallel. This exercise is perfect for improving one's endurance. It is important that the arms and legs move diagonally.

exercises.name: Back Extension
exercises.description: A hyperextension or back extension is an exercise that works the lower back as well as the mid and upper back, specifically the erector spinae.

exercises.name: Incline Bench Press
exercises.description: The bench press is an upper-body weight training exercise in which the trainee presses a weight upwards while lying on a weight training bench.

exercises.name: Shoulder Press
exercises.description: The press, overhead press or shoulder press is a weight training exercise with many variations, typically performed while standing, in which a weight is pressed straight upwards from racking position until the arms are locked out overhead, while the legs, lower back and abs maintain balance.

exercises.name: Skipping
exercises.description: A skipping rope (British English) or jump rope (American English) is a tool used in the sport of skipping/jump rope where one or more participants jump over a rope swung so that it passes under their feet and over their heads.

exercises.name: Side Lateral Raise
exercises.description: The rear delt raise, also known as the rear deltoid raise, or rear shoulder raise is an exercise in weight training.

exercises.name: Sit Ups
exercises.description: The sit-up (or curl-up) is an abdominal endurance training exercise to strengthen and tone the abdominal muscles.

exercises.name: Skater Jumps
exercises.description: Skater Jumps are a great cardio exercise involving jumping in a pattern that shifts your body weight from side to side to create a skating stride.

exercises.name: French Press
exercises.description: Lying triceps extensions, also known as skull crushers and French extensions or French presses, are a strength exercise used in many different forms of strength training.

exercises.name: Triceps Extensions
exercises.description: Lying triceps extensions, also known as skull crushers and French extensions or French presses, are a strength exercise used in many different forms of strength training.

exercises.name: Cool Down
exercises.description: Cooling down (also known as limbering down or warming down) is an easy exercise, done after a more intense activity, to allow the body to gradually transition to a resting or near-resting state.
